            Rated 5 out of
            5
 by
        Williamsburg from
        Researched different options...paint, attempting to re-stain, reface or complete replacement ($$$...
Researched different options...paint, attempting to re-stain, reface or complete replacement ($$$!) of medium walnut raised panel kitchen cabinets that are in good condition otherwise.    There are problems with each option, mentioned in kitchen rehab (often horror) stories on the net.   So I gave this product a try.  Didn't have much to lose, as the finish was deteriorating in various areas, especially around the sink and cutlery drawer.  I used the Restorer in combination with the 0000 steel wool and finished with the Howard polish.   My wife (final judge) said the cabinets look like they did 20-years ago...even in areas where the (poly?) varnish was flaking off.  I think the steel wool helps smooth these flaking areas.   The cabinets have an even color, non-blotchy appearance.   Exceeded my expectations that this was a glorified Old English treatment.     Relatively low odor for a solvent-based product.  Wear gloves and have plenty of rags to wipe off excess product.    Incredibly cheap compared with other restoration choices, presuming you can live with the stain color you have....we can, and we saved a ton of money.
Date published: 2017-07-20





